Ask HN: Interested in Creating a Series of Analysis Videos on Startups
text:
I'm interested in creating a series of snapshot analysis videos on small startups either leveraging A.I. API's such as OpenAI's Davinci, or various AWS/Azure/Google Cloud tools, or startups that have created their own transformer/ML tech and running it straight on the cloud. That being said, I am not sure how to make this interesting or engaging, e.g. entertaining through the YouTube/Video medium.

I really would like to go through and analyze about 25 startups, in video form, I'm going to do it whether I can actually make the videos interesting or not...but, I would love anyone's thoughts on how I can actually improve these videos and make them interesting.

Here's my pilot episode. I have no affiliation with the startup analyzed, Eightify, I just found them on HN and thought it was interesting:

https://youtu.be/1t94qkviuZg

One thing I definitely plan on doing is making future videos between 5-10 minutes long rather than 15.

Please ping me if you know of another startup/small AI/ML company which you would like analyzed. I will not do promotion and need to stay distant from whatever startup video I create, so please provide a link and no other info (otherwise I won't do a video on whatever you send). We can always talk after I create a video on that topic if you would like, but I would like these to all be as, "blind" as possible.

Thank you all in advance.
